{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"coup-teeth-strut","description":"# S2 — Broaden Gerrit replication to change refs (ADR-0010 reversal)\n\nPart of epic 1fa8 (CI as a second Gerrit gate vote via gerrit-to-platform → GitHub Actions).\n\n## Why\nThe GitHub Actions runner must fetch the exact patchset under test. The g2p production pattern\n(ONAP/O-RAN-SC) relies on Gerrit replicating change refs to the GitHub mirror; today\n`infra/gerrit/replication.config` mirrors only `refs/heads/main` + `refs/tags/*` (ADR-0010).\n\n## What\nBroaden replication with a **scoped** change-ref refspec — deliberately NOT a wildcard `refs/*`,\nwhich would replicate `refs/meta/config` (it embeds the webhook token; ADR-0010/0014 keep it off\nGitHub). Record the reversal as an ADR superseding/amending ADR-0010.\n\n## Scope\n- `infra/gerrit/replication.config` (add one scoped refspec line).\n- New ADR superseding/amending ADR-0010; update the refspec table in `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md`.\n- Out of scope: g2p install, credentials, the workflow, the gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Add a scoped `refs/changes/*:refs/changes/*` refspec to `infra/gerrit/replication.config`\n      alongside the existing `refs/heads/main` + `refs/tags/*` lines (NOT wildcard `refs/*`).\n- [ ] Retain `replicatePermissions = false` and ensure `refs/meta/*` is NOT replicated (protects the\n      webhook token per ADR-0014); `checkout-gerrit-change-action`'s `gerrit-url` fallback covers\n      replication lag.\n- [ ] Confirm the GitHub mirror-lock ruleset still bars all non-replication writes to `main`.\n- [ ] Write an ADR superseding/amending **ADR-0010** (replication now includes change refs).\n- [ ] Update the refspec table in `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md`.","id":"ce5a-6a9f-5422-45f6","parent_id":"1fa8-9db4-7c1c-48f3","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S2 — Broaden Gerrit replication to change refs (ADR-0010 reversal)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782956271003700001,"uuid":"d07497f6-11c2-40fc-82a3-41fd5f9da3be"}